    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-10T17:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-10T17:48:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2186: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul in Charge of the Legation in Honduras</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-10T17:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 15—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Honduranean Government requests me to inform the Department of State that
                    from all the information which has been received from the Minister of Honduras
                    in Salvador there is every evidence that the Salvadorean Government is preparing
                    to invade Honduranean territory possibly under the pretext of Honduras having
                    assisted Araujo in his revolutionary movement, which is untrue. … I recommend
                    the Department’s immediate action and attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
